    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="580"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">588.C1/3</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Assistant to the Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hewes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Mr. <persName type="to">Charles S.
                            Haight</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-22">June 22,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Haight</hi>: Replying to yours of June 13:<note
                        n="57" xml:id="d580fn57">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I understand that the Attorney General has rendered an opinion<note n="58"
                        xml:id="d580fn58">37 Op. Atty. Gen. 546.</note> to the effect that the
                    Resolution of March 26 is not mandatory but was intended as a rule of
                    guidance.</p>
                <pb facs="0823" n="723" xml:id="pg_723"/>
                <p>I think the matter of an International Shipping Conference is progressing. The
                    new Committee<note n="59" xml:id="d580fn59">Interdepartmental Shipping Policy
                        Committee.</note> has been at work every day this week to attempt to devise
                    the various facts which must be considered preliminary to developing matters of
                    policy. The question of the advisability and practicability of accomplishing
                    results through an International Conference is being actively pursued.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas Hewes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
